HEADWORD: Noyade
<hw>No`yade"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>noyer</ets> to drown, L. <ets>necare</ets> to kill.]</ety> <def>A
drowning of many persons at once, -- a method of execution practiced at
<city>Nantes</city> in France during the Reign of Terror, by
<person>Jean Baptiste Carrier</person>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

